00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:48,323
VR offers unique challenges, but also unique opportunities.

325
00:16:49,143 --> 00:16:51,605
In VR, the player is the camera, and by that definition,

326
00:16:51,685 --> 00:16:52,946
free to look at whatever they like.

327
00:16:53,626 --> 00:16:55,708
I spoke earlier about trying to keep the players focused

328
00:16:55,748 --> 00:16:56,828
on their role in the story.

329
00:16:57,669 --> 00:17:00,151
But with the free camera, it does give us opportunities

330
00:17:00,191 --> 00:17:01,752
to put nice details on characters

331
00:17:01,792 --> 00:17:03,233
that hopefully players will notice.

332
00:17:05,555 --> 00:17:08,276
The avatar, for example, the avatar hands, for example,

333
00:17:08,316 --> 00:17:10,138
are something we expect players to scrutinize.

334
00:17:10,618 --> 00:17:10,778
So.

335
00:17:12,012 --> 00:17:14,033
If you hold them up and flex your fingers,

336
00:17:14,173 --> 00:17:16,835
you'll see wrinkle maps and mesh blend shapes changing,

337
00:17:17,275 --> 00:17:19,116
so knuckles and tendons appear on the skin

338
00:17:19,237 --> 00:17:20,818
and the skin wrinkles realistically.

339
00:17:21,798 --> 00:17:23,299
We also created blood flow maps

340
00:17:23,339 --> 00:17:25,221
to simulate color changes in the skin.

341
00:17:25,921 --> 00:17:27,722
So for example, the knuckles whiten

342
00:17:27,742 --> 00:17:29,223
when the hand is drawn into a fist.

343
00:17:41,695 --> 00:17:46,519
Adding details on characters are also great storytelling devices, especially in VR.

344
00:17:46,719 --> 00:17:50,362
Easter eggs that allude or give hints to the history or backstory of a character.

345
00:17:53,184 --> 00:17:57,367
Adding details, players that will hopefully notice and wonder about their meaning or significance.

346
00:17:57,928 --> 00:17:59,890
